1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:04,130
the following story is fictional and does
not depict any actual person or event.

2
00:00:10,670 --> 00:00:14,680
March 22,1964.

3
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:20,550
I forgot to pack my flannel pj's 
and my rabbit-hair slippers.

4
00:00:20,890 --> 00:00:22,750
Maybe I can bring them to her,Bill?

5
00:00:22,850 --> 00:00:23,940
We talked about this.

6
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:25,850
No visits.

7
00:00:29,930 --> 00:00:31,690
I gotta use the kybo.

8
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:34,320
- What did she say?
- She needs the bathroom.

9
00:00:34,410 --> 00:00:35,750
You'll have to hold it.

10
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,950
And speak English,Hilary.

11
00:00:38,090 --> 00:00:40,280
If I could take it back,I would.

12
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:43,800
It's just... no one told us it could happen,you know?

13
00:00:43,850 --> 00:00:46,910
Let's not talk about it,honey.Please?

14
00:00:47,010 --> 00:00:48,680
I'm sorry,Mom.

15
00:00:58,340 --> 00:00:59,680
Here we are.

16
00:01:01,580 --> 00:01:04,250
Looks even prettier than the brochure.

17
00:01:05,010 --> 00:01:07,820
I'm sure everyone will be very nice.

18
00:01:18,580 --> 00:01:20,870
Please don't leave me here.

19
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:23,640
I'll make sure no one sees me at home,Daddy,I swear.

20
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:24,610
Patricia.

21
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,610
Come on,Hilary.

22
00:01:41,370 --> 00:01:42,280
Huck said he'd marry me.

23
00:01:42,330 --> 00:01:44,160
Huck's a child. So are you.

24
00:01:44,220 --> 00:01:45,980
But it's our baby. (sighs)

25
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:48,510
Do you have any idea what it's like to raise a child?

26
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:51,710
Now,please,Hilary,I know what's best.

27
00:01:53,610 --> 00:01:55,140
Will you visit me,Mom?

28
00:01:55,190 --> 00:01:56,290
We'll see,sweetheart.

29
00:01:56,340 --> 00:01:57,060
Get in the car,Patricia.

30
00:01:57,110 --> 00:01:58,850
You're not coming in?!

31
00:02:00,140 --> 00:02:02,040
She's never spent a night away from home,Bill.

32
00:02:02,140 --> 00:02:02,970
And if you'd watched her better,

33
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:05,740
she wouldn't be in this mess in the first place.

34
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:11,550
Please don't leave me here.

35
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:16,510
Mommy?

36
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:19,810
My mom passed away two months ago.

37
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:25,290
She was a great mother,but...I found this in her belongings.

38
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:30,010
Your birth certificate?

39
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:32,490
My original birth certificate.

40
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:36,020
I never knew,but I was adopted.

41
00:03:36,690 --> 00:03:39,210
You know we deal in homicides,right,Ms. Lakey?

42
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:41,410
I tracked down my real mother.

43
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:44,320
She was murdered the day after I was born.

44
00:03:44,370 --> 00:03:45,850
Her name was Hilary West.

45
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,760
She was 17 years old.

46
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,850
Never found the doer.

47
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:53,240
I was hoping if you did,
you might be able to tell me...

48
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:55,530
Why she gave you up?

49
00:03:55,580 --> 00:03:57,970
- Yes.
- Your mom was 17.

50
00:03:58,070 --> 00:03:59,930
Probably couldn't raise you the way she wanted.

51
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:01,600
I have a nine-year-old son.

52
00:04:01,650 --> 00:04:03,590
I can't even fathom doing something like that.

53
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:06,150
Yeah.Times were different.

54
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:09,340
Are you... close with your mother?

55
00:04:12,390 --> 00:04:15,100
People shouldn't have kids till they're ready.

56
00:04:15,770 --> 00:04:17,630
Sounds like your mother wasn't.

57
00:04:17,730 --> 00:04:20,400
Still,I'd like to know.

58
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:26,920
Well,this is from St. Mary's Home for Unwed Mothers.

59
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:28,360
Where she gave birth.

60
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:31,040
There's no mention of St. Mary's in the article.

61
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:33,150
Maybe they were keeping it out of the press?

62
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:34,550
Maybe they didn't know.

63
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:38,030
How's that possible?She was there right before she died.

64
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,890
Could be someone was keeping it secret.

65
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:43,710
Who?

66
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:47,300
Someone with a secret of their own.

